column12: Lubricious coatings
column13: The present invention relates to lubricious coatings comprising an ionomer and a hydrophilic polymer wherein the ionomer is cross-linked using a suitable cross-linking agent, and optionally also conventional excipients, such as a surfactant, a plasticizer and/or a filler. The invention also relates to pharmaceutical products covered by such lubricious coatings, compositions for preparing these lubricious coatings and a method for providing pharmaceutical products with these lubricious coatings.

column13: Embodiments disclosed herein provide systems, methods and computer readable media for generating remote views in a virtual mobile device platform. A virtual mobile device platform may be coupled to a physical mobile device over a network and generate frames of data for generating views on the physical device. These frames can be generated using an efficient display encoding pipeline on the virtual mobile device platform. Such efficiencies may include, for example, the synchronization of various processes or operations, the governing of various processing rates, the elimination of duplicative or redundant processing, the application of different encoding schemes, the efficient detection of duplicative or redundant data or the combination of certain operations.

column13: resumo revestimentos lubrificados a presente invenção está relacionada a revestimentos lubrificados compreendendo um ionômero e um polímero hidrofílico, onde o ionômero é ligado de forma cruzada utilizando um agente de ligação cruzada adequado, e opcionalmente, excipientes convencionais, tais como um surfactante, um plastificante e/ou um agente de enchimento. a invenção também está relacionada aos produtos farmacêuticos recobertos por tais revestimentos lubrificados, às composições para preparo destes revestimentos, e a um método para fornecimento destes produtos com estes revestimentos.

column12: Lift axle control unit for lift axle suspension system of vehicle
column13: A lift axle control unit (2) for a lift axle suspension system of a vehicle is provided. The lift axle control unit includes a supply input port (8) connected to a pressure reservoir; a load detectionvalve (7) connected to the supply input port, with the load detection valve being connectable to load variable parts of the vehicle and delivering a first pressure signal in dependence of an axle load of the vehicle; a pneumatic damping device (14) providing a second pressure signal; a first relay valve (11) for feeding a suspension bellow (2) of the vehicle; a second relay valve (12) which is areverse-direction relay valve and is used for feeding a lift bellow of a lift axle of the vehicle. In order to advantageously adjust damping characteristics according to proper hardware requirements,a solenoid device (10) is connected to the load detection valve (7) to transmit the first pressure signal (p1) to transfer the first pressure signal to the relay valves, wherein the solenoid device (10) is controlled by an electric control signal (S1) generated according to the second pressure signal (p2).

column12: A system for super resolution using deep learning
column13: A system for super resolution using deep learning The present invention relates to super resolution using deep learning. The proposed invention comprises SRCNN, WDSR, DCSCN and SRGAN.Super-resolution (SR) technique reconstructs a higher-resolution image or sequence from the observed LR images. As SR has been a major sector of research in this domain, a lot of work is being done on this technique. Both multi-frame and single-frame SR have significant applications in our daily life. The proposed invention provides a review of SR from the perspective of different techniques used and their applications, and especially the main contributions given in this domain. Technical details are discussed in this report, including reconstruction models, parameter selection methods, optimization algorithms and their result comparison. Moreover, an exhaustive summary of the current applications using SR techniques has been presented.Thedifferent network structures and parameter settings to achieve tradeoffs between performance and speed. Following invention described in details with the help of figure 1 of sheet 1 illustrates algorithm of how a super resolution technique works.
